                p Returning to our <code class="inline-code">handleSubmit</code> function, we now start a <code class="inline-code">for</code> loop, which iterates over our <code class="inline-code">myTodos</code> aray. For each todo element within our <code class="inline-code">myTodos</code> array, we instantiate a new <code class="inline-code">newTodo</code> variable, calling on the <code class="inline-code">document</code>'s <code class="inline-code">createElement()</code> method, and pass it the string <em>"li"</em>. As this syntax indicates, we are creating a new list item. In our HTML document, this would be equivalent to creating an emtpy <code class="inline-code">&ltli&gt</code> element:
